'''Bryntail lead mine''' is a disused [[lead]] [[Metal mining in Wales|mine]] near [[Llanidloes]] in [[Powys]], [[Wales]]. <ref>[http://www.llanidloes.com/heritage/index.html Llanidloes heritage]</ref> It is in the care of [[Cadw]]. [[Image:Badgernet Clywedog reservoir 1.JPG|right|thumb|Bryntail and [[Clywedog reservoir]] dam, footbridge bottom left]] There were three main shafts, Murray's, Gundry's and Western shaft. The majority of the scheduled buildings on the site are associated with Gundry's shaft, including a [[baryte | barytes]] mill, two crushing houses, ore bins, roasting ovens and water tanks. On the eastern dressing floor are [[jigger box]] placements, three buddles, two more ore bins and washing and picking floors. Other mine buildings include the manager's office, [[Forge|smithy]], store buildings and a [[circular magazine]], as well as the miners' footbridge.
