'''Matupi Cave''' is a cave in the Mount Hoyo [[massif]] of the [[Ituri Rainforest]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], where archaeologists have found evidence for [[Later Stone Age]] human occupation spanning over 40,000 years.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Noten|first=Francis Van|date=1977-03-01|title=Excavations at Matupi cave|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/antiquity/article/excavations-at-matupi-cave/1BC62EB1BE9150DDDDBB1342FFB99D82|journal=Antiquity|volume=51|issue=201|pages=35–40|doi=10.1017/S0003598X00100572|issn=0003-598X}}</ref> The cave has some of the earliest evidence in the world for [[Microlith|microlithic]] tool technologies.<ref>{{Cite book|title=A Dictionary of Archaeology|last=Shaw|first=Ian|last2=Jameson|first2=Robert|publisher=Blackwell|year=1999|isbn=|location=|pages=30|quote=|via=}}</ref>   

